mqtt2sqlite
===========

Robust MQTT->SQLite collector.

Env vars:
  MQTT_BROKER (default 127.0.0.1, the broker on the FRITZ!Box)
  MQTT_PORT (default 1883)
  MQTT_TOPICS (comma- or whitespace-separated topics)
  MQTT_TOPIC (legacy single topic; default # if no topics are otherwise set)
  MQTT_DB_PATH (default ./mqtt_messages.db)
  NETWORK_FIX_SCRIPT (default ./handle_network_error.sh)
  RECONNECT_MIN_S (default 2)
  RECONNECT_MAX_S (default 60)
  RETRY_SLEEP_AFTER_SCRIPT_S (default 5)
  MQTT_LOG_INSERTS (set to 1 to log inserts)

Binary installed to:
  /usr/bin/mqtt_to_sqlite

Topics may also be supplied with a repeatable command-line option:
  mqtt_to_sqlite -t '+/power/get' -t '+/energycounter/get'

Topic precedence:
  1. Repeated -t/--topic arguments
  2. MQTT_TOPICS
  3. MQTT_TOPIC
  4. #

The collector creates a messages table with Unix-second timestamps, topic,
payload, QoS, and retain flag. SQLite uses WAL mode so a read-only client such
as mqtt-grafana can query the database while messages are being inserted.

For persistent storage on a FRITZ!Box, set MQTT_DB_PATH to an absolute path on
mounted USB storage. Ensure the storage is mounted before starting the
collector. Set MQTT_LOG_INSERTS=1 for per-message diagnostic logging.
